" clear=3D"both"> <span id=3D"zWPZa4" class=3D"z-html"><p>The <strong>Volum=
e of the Frustum of a Cone</strong> calculator&nbsp;computes the volume of =
a frustum (slice) of a cone based<img alt=3D"" src=3D"https://www.vcalc.com=
/attachments/e6cc9bde-da27-11e2-8e97-bc764e04d25f/ConeFrustumVolume-illustr=
ation.png" style=3D"float:right; height:157px; width:150px"> on the top rad=
ius (<strong>a</strong>), bottom radius (<strong>b</strong>) and height (<s=
trong>h</strong>) in between.&nbsp;</p>=20
<p><strong>INSTRUCTION:</strong> Choose units and enter the following:</p>=
=20
<ul>=20
 <li>(<strong>a</strong>) - radius of top surface</li>=20
 <li>(<strong>b</strong>) - radius of bottom surface</li>=20
 <li>(<strong>h</strong>) - height in between top and bottom</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p><strong>Volume of the Cone Section (V):</strong> &nbsp;The calculator co=
mputes the volume (<strong>V</strong>) in cubic meters (m<sup>3</sup>). &nb=
sp;However this can be automatically converted to many other volume units (=
e.g. gallons or cubic feet) via the pull-down menu.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>=20
<h3><span>The Math</span></h3>=20
<p>The frustum of a cone is a section of a cone also known as a truncated c=
one. The frustum of a cone is created by parallel planes that go through th=
e cone and are normal (perpendicular) to the center axis of the cone. &nbsp=
;The shape of the top and bottom are perfect circles whose centers are dire=
ctly aligned. &nbsp;The planes are separated by the height (h). The <span c=
lass=3D"wikiexternallink"><a href=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/wiki/vCalc/Cone-=
Frustum-Volume" target=3D"_self">formula for the Volume of the Frustum of a=
 cone</a></span> is as follows:</p>=20
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=3D"wik=
iexternallink"><a href=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/wiki/vCalc/Cone-Frustum-Vol=
ume" target=3D"_self"><strong>V =3D <sup>1</sup>/<sub>3</sub> =E2=80=A2 =CF=
=80 =E2=80=A2 h(a<sup>2</sup>+a=E2=80=A2b+b<sup>2</sup>)</strong></a></span=
>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>=20
<p>where:<img alt=3D"/attachments/e6cc9bde-da27-11e2-8e97-bc764e04d25f/Cone=
FrustumVolume-illustration.png" src=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/attachments/e6=
cc9bde-da27-11e2-8e97-bc764e04d25f/ConeFrustumVolume-illustration.png" styl=
e=3D"float:right; height:157px; width:149px">&nbsp;</p>=20
<ul>=20
 <li>V is the <span class=3D"wikiexternallink"><a href=3D"https://www.vcalc=
.com/wiki/vCalc/Cone-Frustum-Volume" target=3D"_self">volume of the frustum=
 (section) of a cone</a></span></li>=20
 <li>a is the radius of one end</li>=20
 <li>b is the radius of the other end</li>=20
 <li>h is the height</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p><a href=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/wikiclip/?uuid=3D6aafc1bb-5c95-11ee-b65=
f-bc764e203090" style=3D"float:right;"><img src=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/st=
